1---Why is Java considered more object-oriented than C++?

Answer:

Both Java and C++ support object-oriented programming. However, Java is designed primarily around classes and objects, 
whereas C++ supports both procedural and object-oriented programming. In Java, almost everything 
is organized inside classes, while in C++ you can write programs without using classes.
